FBIS4-58672 "drnes088_j_94008" FBIS-NES-94-088 Daily Report 4 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Fighting Continues; Airport Bombed; Calls for Peace Made Fighting Continues; Airport Bombed; Calls for Peace Made Defense Ministry Appeals for Unity EA0505200094 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 2045 GMT 4 May 94 EA0505200094 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Excerpts] A responsible source at the Defense Ministry has stated the following: In continuation of the scenario prepared by the gang of al-Ahmar, whose bloody appetite was stimulated after the aggression against the 3d Armored Brigade in 'Imran, this bloody gang of al-Ahmar, which thirsts for blood and devastation, at 8:15 tonight began to attack the Martyr Ba Suhayb Brigade Camp in Dhamar town. This daring brigade, in these decisive historic moments, is waging a fierce war against the enemies of the homeland and is confronting with bravery, death, and defiance the mercenaries of the adventurist gang of al-Ahmar. [passage omitted] While the Defense Ministry deals with this crime, it assures the masses of our Yemeni people that it will remain loyal to the pledge by individuals of our armed forces to protect our people and their national and democratic options. In these historic moments, it calls on all the honorable sons of our people, the heroes of their Armed Forces and the generous forces to stand united to confront this imminent danger to the homeland and its unity, and inflict defeat on the bloody gang of al-Ahmar. Our people are lying in wait for them.
